{"title_page": "Paul Grilley", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n | name        = Paul Grilley\n | image       = <!-- just filename, no File: -->\n | caption     =\n | birth_date  = c. 1959<!-- {{Birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n | birth_place =\n | death_date  = <!-- {{d-da|9 September 1901|12 May 1856}}  (death date then birth date) -->\n | death_place =\n | nationality = American\n | known_for   = [[Yin Yoga]]\n | occupation  = [[Modern yoga|Yoga]] teacher\n | spouse      = {{marriage|[[Patti Davis]]|1984|1990|end=div}} <br> Suzee Grilley\n}}\n'''Paul Grilley''' is a teacher of [[modern yoga]] known for helping, along with [[Sarah Powers]], to develop the slow-paced style, [[Yin Yoga]]. He and his wife Suzee Grilley train teachers in Yin Yoga.\n\n==Education==\n\nPaul Grilley began to practise yoga in 1979, starting to study anatomy in Montana that same year. In 1982 he went on to study [[anatomy]] and [[kinesiology]] at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]]. He gained his master's degree at [[St John's College, Santa Fe]] in 2000. He was awarded an honorary Ph.D. by  the California Institute for Human Science for his work on the relevance of [[fascia]], the sheets of [[connective tissue]] that hold the body together, to the practice of yoga asanas.<ref name=Bernie>{{cite book |last=Clark |first=Bernie |title=The Complete Guide to Yin yoga |year=2012 |publisher=White Cloud Press |isbn=978-1-935952-50-3 |pp=21\u201322}}</ref><ref name=\"Yoga U\">{{cite web |title=Working with the Fascia in Yoga: Online Yoga Talk with Yin Yoga Teacher Paul Grilley |url=https://www.yogauonline.com/yoga-anatomy/working-fascia-yoga-online-yoga-talk-yin-yoga-teacher-paul-grilley |publisher=Yoga U |accessdate=5 May 2019 |date=2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nHe studied the slow-paced, less aggressive form of [[modern yoga]] called [[Yin Yoga]] under its creator, [[Paulie Zink]], and later assisted with its development.<ref name=kinosian>{{cite news |title=Yin yoga: yang-style's less aggressive counterpart: Taoist-based practice targets the connective tissues, ligaments, joints and synovial fluid |author=Janet Kinosian |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/sep/21/health/he-yin-yoga21 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]  |date=Sep 21, 2009 |accessdate=January 6, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Lisa Maria 82\">{{cite news |title=Soothe Yourself |author=Lisa Maria |url=http://www.yogajournal.com/practice/2677 |page=82 |newspaper=[[Yoga Journal]] |date=Sep 2008 |accessdate=January 6, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Achy Joints? How Yin Yoga Can Help\">{{cite journal |last1=Gamerman |first1=Amy |title=Achy Joints? How Yin Yoga Can Help |journal=The Oprah Magazine |date=June 2012 |volume=13 |issue=6 |accessdate=6 July 2015 |quote='Yin yoga is joint rehabilitation,' says Paul Grilley, the godfather of the movement. |url=http://www.oprah.com/health/Yin-Yoga-Good-for-Joints-Slower-Yoga}}</ref>{{sfn|Grilley|2012|p=xiii}} \n\nGrilley taught yoga to [[Sarah Powers]], who devised the name \"Yin Yoga\" and went on to develop her own variant of it, [[Insight Yoga]]. Grilley had until then described the form as \"Taoist Yoga\".<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Maria |first1=Lisa |title=Insider's Guide--A veteran teacher explores the depths of yoga and self-inquiry, creating a manual for inner peace |journal=[[Yoga Journal]] |date=Feb 2009 |pages=111\u2013112}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kragie |first1=Eileen |title=Yin yoga: The Complete Art Form Founded by Paulie Zink |journal=[[Elephant Journal]] |date=June 27, 2014 |url=http://www.elephantjournal.com/2014/06/yin-yoga-the-complete-art-form-founded-by-master-paulie-zink-eileen-kragie/ |accessdate=3 July 2015 | quote=Paulie refers to his art as Yin and Yang yoga, but often uses the term 'Yin yoga' for short.}}</ref> He teaches Yin Yoga and trains yoga teachers with his wife Suzee Grilley. Their Yin Yoga curriculum covers the [[human anatomy]] of bones and muscles as well as seven [[asana]]s that they describe as [[archetypal]], [[yoga]] and [[meditation]].<ref name=\"PG\">{{cite web |title=Yin Yoga Teacher Training |url=http://paulgrilley.com/ |publisher=Paul Grilley |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> He serves as a master teacher at Pranamaya.<ref name=\"Pranamaya\">{{cite web |title=Meet Your Instructors |url=https://pranamaya.com/master-teachers/ |publisher=Pranamaya |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> From his knowledge of anatomy, Grilley states that it is not possible for everyone to do all asanas, because of variations in the shapes of specific bones; for example, some people have a much longer neck on the [[femur]] (thigh bone) than others, giving them, he argues, greater freedom of movement in the [[hip joint]].<ref name=\"Yoga Chicago\">{{cite web |last1=Om |first1=Kali |title=Anatomy and Yin Yoga with Paul Grilley |url=http://yogachicago.com/2014/03/anatomy-and-yin-yoga-with-paul-grilley/ |publisher=Yoga Chicago |accessdate=5 May 2019 |date=January 2007}}</ref> \n\nGrilley has stated that Yin Yoga is not a franchise or hybrid like Aqua Yoga or Disco Yoga, and the use of the term is not restricted by copyright or trademark; instead, it is an additional way of practising.<ref name=\"YJ 2003\">{{cite journal |last1=Solan |first1=Matthew |title=Talking Shop with Paul Grilley |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vOkDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA24 |journal=[[Yoga Journal]] |issue=May/June 2003 |date=May 2003 |page=24}}</ref>\n\nGrilley has been interviewed and featured in magazines including ''[[Yoga Journal]]''<ref name=\"YJ 2003\"/> and ''Elephant Journal'',<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pucelle |first1=Sebastian |title=Interview with Yin Yoga Teachers Paul & Suzee Grilley |url=https://www.elephantjournal.com/2013/04/interview-with-yin-yoga-teachers-paul-suzee-grilley/ |publisher=Elephant Journal |accessdate=5 May 2019 |date=7 April 2013}}</ref> and in chapters of books such as Victoria Bailey's 2012 ''Sharing Sadhana'': Bailey describes him as both spiritual, as seen in his DVD on ''Chakra Theory and Meditation'', and knowledgeable about the anatomical basis of yoga.<ref name=\"Bailey 2012\">{{cite book |author=Bailey, Victoria |title=Sharing Sadhana: Insights and Inspiration for a Personal Yoga Practice |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HYTTBvOmtNsC&pg=PA1 |year=2012 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1-4422-1382-1 |pages=1\u20138}}</ref>\n\n[[File:The Reagan Family at Rancho Del Cielo.jpg|thumb|Grilley and his first wife [[Patti Davis]] (at right) with the [[Ronald Reagan|Reagan]] family at Rancho Del Cielo, 1985. Courtesy Ronald Reagan Library]]\n\n==Personal life==\n\nIn 1984, he married [[Patti Davis]], daughter of US president [[Ronald Reagan]]. They divorced in 1990 and had no children.<ref name=\"People05181992\">{{cite journal |first=J. D. |last=Podolsky |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20112711,00.html |title=A Daughter's Lament |journal=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=18 May 1992 |accessdate=30 March 2013}}</ref> He then married Suzee Grilley (b. 1959); she is a Registered Yoga Teacher who has also taught [[Capoeira]] and [[modern dance]].<ref name=YA>{{cite web |title=About Suzee Grilley |url=https://www.yogaalliance.org/TeacherPublicProfile/tid/86567 |publisher=Yoga Alliance |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref><ref name=YE>{{cite web |title=Cherise Richards |url=https://www.yogaenlightened.com/team/cherise-richards/ |publisher=Yoga Enlightened |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> They live in [[Ashland, Oregon]].<ref name=YA/>\n\n==Works==\n\n* {{cite media |publisher=Pranamaya |title=Anatomy for Yoga with Paul Grilley (DVD) |date=2004 |isbn= \t978-1585651689 |oclc=56924405 |url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/anatomy-for-yoga/oclc/56924405}}\n* {{cite book |last=Grilley |first=Paul |author-mask=0 |title=Yin Yoga: Principles and Practice |year=2012 |publisher=White Cloud Press |location=Ashland, Oregon |isbn=9781935952701 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book | last=Grilley | first=Paul |author-mask=0 | title=A Yogi's Guide to Chakra Meditation | publisher=Cardinal | year=2019 | isbn=978-1-7335839-0-9 | oclc=1089967309}}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{official website|http://paulgrilley.com/}}\n\n{{Modern yoga}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grilley, Paul}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:American yoga teachers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n | name        = Paul Grilley\n | image       = <!-- just filename, no File: -->\n | caption     =\n | birth_date  = c. 1959<!-- {{Birth date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n | birth_place =\n | death_date  = <!-- {{d-da|9 September 1901|12 May 1856}}  (death date then birth date) -->\n | death_place =\n | nationality = American\n | known_for   = [[Yin Yoga]]\n | occupation  = [[Modern yoga|Yoga]] teacher\n | spouse      = {{marriage|[[Patti Davis]]|1984|1990|end=div}} <br> Suzee Grilley\n}}\n'''Paul Grilley''' is a teacher of [[modern yoga]] known for helping, along with [[Sarah Powers]], to develop the slow-paced style, [[Yin Yoga]]. He and his wife Suzee Grilley train teachers in Yin Yoga.\n\n==Education==\n\nPaul Grilley began to practise yoga in 1979, starting to study anatomy in Montana that same year. In 1982 he went on to study [[anatomy]] and [[kinesiology]] at the [[University of California, Los Angeles]]. He gained his master's degree at [[St John's College, Santa Fe]] in 2000. He was awarded an honorary Ph.D. by  the California Institute for Human Science for his work on the relevance of [[fascia]], the sheets of [[connective tissue]] that hold the body together, to the practice of yoga asanas.<ref name=Bernie>{{cite book |last=Clark |first=Bernie |title=The Complete Guide to Yin yoga |year=2012 |publisher=White Cloud Press |isbn=978-1-935952-50-3 |pp=21\u201322}}</ref><ref name=\"Yoga U\">{{cite web |title=Working with the Fascia in Yoga: Online Yoga Talk with Yin Yoga Teacher Paul Grilley |url=https://www.yogauonline.com/yoga-anatomy/working-fascia-yoga-online-yoga-talk-yin-yoga-teacher-paul-grilley |publisher=Yoga U |accessdate=5 May 2019 |date=2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\nHe studied the slow-paced, less aggressive form of [[modern yoga]] called [[Yin Yoga]] under its creator, [[Paulie Zink]], and later assisted with its development.<ref name=kinosian>{{cite news |title=Yin yoga: yang-style's less aggressive counterpart: Taoist-based practice targets the connective tissues, ligaments, joints and synovial fluid |author=Janet Kinosian |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2009/sep/21/health/he-yin-yoga21 |newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]  |date=Sep 21, 2009 |accessdate=January 6, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Lisa Maria 82\">{{cite news |title=Soothe Yourself |author=Lisa Maria |url=http://www.yogajournal.com/practice/2677 |page=82 |newspaper=[[Yoga Journal]] |date=Sep 2008 |accessdate=January 6, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Achy Joints? How Yin Yoga Can Help\">{{cite journal |last1=Gamerman |first1=Amy |title=Achy Joints? How Yin Yoga Can Help |journal=The Oprah Magazine |date=June 2012 |volume=13 |issue=6 |accessdate=6 July 2015 |quote='Yin yoga is joint rehabilitation,' says Paul Grilley, the godfather of the movement. |url=http://www.oprah.com/health/Yin-Yoga-Good-for-Joints-Slower-Yoga}}</ref>{{sfn|Grilley|2012|p=xiii}} \n\nGrilley taught yoga to [[Sarah Powers]], who devised the name \"Yin Yoga\" and went on to develop her own variant of it, [[Insight Yoga]]. Grilley had until then described the form as \"Taoist Yoga\".<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Maria |first1=Lisa |title=Insider's Guide--A veteran teacher explores the depths of yoga and self-inquiry, creating a manual for inner peace |journal=[[Yoga Journal]] |date=Feb 2009 |pages=111\u2013112}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kragie |first1=Eileen |title=Yin yoga: The Complete Art Form Founded by Paulie Zink |journal=[[Elephant Journal]] |date=June 27, 2014 |url=http://www.elephantjournal.com/2014/06/yin-yoga-the-complete-art-form-founded-by-master-paulie-zink-eileen-kragie/ |accessdate=3 July 2015 | quote=Paulie refers to his art as Yin and Yang yoga, but often uses the term 'Yin yoga' for short.}}</ref> He teaches Yin Yoga and trains yoga teachers with his wife Suzee Grilley. Their Yin Yoga curriculum covers the [[human anatomy]] of bones and muscles as well as seven [[asana]]s that they describe as [[archetypal]], [[yoga]] and [[meditation]].<ref name=\"PG\">{{cite web |title=Yin Yoga Teacher Training |url=http://paulgrilley.com/ |publisher=Paul Grilley |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> He serves as a master teacher at Pranamaya.<ref name=\"Pranamaya\">{{cite web |title=Meet Your Instructors |url=https://pranamaya.com/master-teachers/ |publisher=Pranamaya |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> From his knowledge of anatomy, Grilley states that it is not possible for everyone to do all asanas, because of variations in the shapes of specific bones; for example, some people have a much longer neck on the [[femur]] (thigh bone) than others, giving them, he argues, greater freedom of movement in the [[hip joint]].<ref name=\"Yoga Chicago\">{{cite web |last1=Om |first1=Kali |title=Anatomy and Yin Yoga with Paul Grilley |url=http://yogachicago.com/2014/03/anatomy-and-yin-yoga-with-paul-grilley/ |publisher=Yoga Chicago |accessdate=5 May 2019 |date=January 2007}}</ref> \n\nGrilley has stated that Yin Yoga is not a franchise or hybrid like Aqua Yoga or Disco Yoga, and the use of the term is not restricted by copyright or trademark; instead, it is an additional way of practising.<ref name=\"YJ 2003\">{{cite journal |last1=Solan |first1=Matthew |title=Talking Shop with Paul Grilley |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=vOkDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA24 |journal=[[Yoga Journal]] |issue=May/June 2003 |date=May 2003 |page=24}}</ref>\n\nGrilley has been interviewed and featured in magazines including ''[[Yoga Journal]]''<ref name=\"YJ 2003\"/> and ''Elephant Journal'',<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pucelle |first1=Sebastian |title=Interview with Yin Yoga Teachers Paul & Suzee Grilley |url=https://www.elephantjournal.com/2013/04/interview-with-yin-yoga-teachers-paul-suzee-grilley/ |publisher=Elephant Journal |accessdate=5 May 2019 |date=7 April 2013}}</ref> and in chapters of books such as Victoria Bailey's 2012 ''Sharing Sadhana'': Bailey describes him as both spiritual, as seen in his DVD on ''Chakra Theory and Meditation'', and knowledgeable about the anatomical basis of yoga.<ref name=\"Bailey 2012\">{{cite book |author=Bailey, Victoria |title=Sharing Sadhana: Insights and Inspiration for a Personal Yoga Practice |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HYTTBvOmtNsC&pg=PA1 |year=2012 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1-4422-1382-1 |pages=1\u20138}}</ref>\n\n[[File:The Reagan Family at Rancho Del Cielo.jpg|thumb|Grilley and his first wife [[Patti Davis]] (at right) with the [[Ronald Reagan|Reagan]] family at Rancho Del Cielo, 1985. Courtesy Ronald Reagan Library]]\n\n==Personal life==\n\nIn 1984, he married [[Patti Davis]], daughter of US president [[Ronald Reagan]]. They divorced in 1990 and had no children.<ref name=\"People05181992\">{{cite journal |first=J. D. |last=Podolsky |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20112711,00.html |title=A Daughter's Lament |journal=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=18 May 1992 |accessdate=30 March 2013}}</ref> He then married Suzee Grilley (b. 1959); she is a Registered Yoga Teacher who has also taught [[Capoeira]] and [[modern dance]].<ref name=YA>{{cite web |title=About Suzee Grilley |url=https://www.yogaalliance.org/TeacherPublicProfile/tid/86567 |publisher=Yoga Alliance |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref><ref name=YE>{{cite web |title=Cherise Richards |url=https://www.yogaenlightened.com/team/cherise-richards/ |publisher=Yoga Enlightened |accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> They live in [[Ashland, Oregon]].<ref name=YA/>\n\n==Works==\n\n* {{cite media |publisher=Pranamaya |title=Anatomy for Yoga with Paul Grilley (DVD) |date=2004 |isbn= \t978-1585651689 |oclc=56924405 |url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/anatomy-for-yoga/oclc/56924405}}\n* {{cite book |last=Grilley |first=Paul |author-mask=0 |title=Yin Yoga: Principles and Practice |year=2012 |publisher=White Cloud Press |location=Ashland, Oregon |isbn=9781935952701 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book | last=Grilley | first=Paul |author-mask=0 | title=A Yogi's Guide to Chakra Meditation | publisher=Cardinal | year=2019 | isbn=978-1-7335839-0-9 | oclc=1089967309}}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{official website|http://paulgrilley.com/}}\n\n{{Modern yoga}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:American yoga teachers]]\n", "name_user": "DB1729", "label": "safe", "comment": "default sort", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Grilley"}
